rComments: So.......i'm a native quebecer french and he speaks French in that class .. BUT still I can't really understand his accent even when I'm really concentrating he's talking really fast and reading his powerpoint for the whole semester....
Where's our grades bro?? its been 3 months

Honestly, for waisitng my time he is a good teacher. Good luck to understand the link between his powerpoints (really precise, clear and link to the lessons) and what he says (for real, we became mad at him for that point). Besides, be patient, he may be late, again, and again for no reason

WORST TEACHER EVER. During his third class, he already had 3 complaints from students that were unsatisfied with his way of teaching. He is absolutely NOT clear, he speaks very fast. His material doesn't make sens at all . When he speaks, nothing fits with the powerpoint. He has grammatical errors in all his documents. Not enough space to continu

He is friendly, but I don't think he should be a prof. First of all, his course materials are full of grammar errors. Second, he doesn't seem to care about his students at all. In a one-month condensed course, he asked us to finish five summaries, one short individual paper, one long individual paper and one group project.

His english is VERY poor both verbally and written. Slideshows are often difficult to understand since is full of grammar and spelling mistakes. Seems as though he copy and pasted it from google translate. His marking criteria is often vague and grades much harder than expected on essays. I have a 9.2 CGPA and this class brought down my GPA alot.

He really cares for his students and wants them to succeed, but his powerpoints can be confusing. You don't need to bother with the readings and the midterm and the projects are very straightforward, he tells you exactly what to study and what he expects and the final is take home. Boring class but overall good guy who really cares for his students
Too many readings per week. Entertaining Lecturer. Allows us to practice what we learned in class through activities.

Professor Banyongen, while friendly, is not a good teacher. His slides are often unintelligible, and it is hard to understand him when he lectures. He consistently assigns over 100 pages of reading every week. He only lectures, despite this being a seminar. His grading criteria are very unclear and his syllabus is often self-contradictory.

His accent is SO hard to understand but he makes and posts detailed powerpoints.  He constantly says no one pays attention, somewhat true though. One short assignment (easy), a mid term (answer 2 out of 5 questions, again easy material), and a final group project (fairly easy).  No textbook, no final exam, no reason to read the posted articles.

there's one group project which counts as your final. Which is great because one less final exam to worry about. 1 individual paper just 200 words& a midterm. He's amazing when it comes to feedback. If you need ANYTHING at all, u can email him & he replies within seconds. He's the absolute sweetest. Also, he makes you sign a paper for attendance.
Cool prof. You just have to show interest and show up as the powerpoints may be vague at times

Wouldn't recommend anyone to take any classes with this professor. He is very tough to understand because of his heavy accent. The course is also very disorganized. He changed the syllabus like 4 times in the semester. He takes attendance in every class, but the tests are pretty much right from the slides.

Very knowledgeable and wants his students to succeed, it's just very hard when he has such a thick accent that it's hard to understand what the question is when he was looking for participation. Assignments were given a lot of useful feedback. Readings were useless, don't even bother as they weren't on slides or exam. Takes attendance for marks!

While it was difficult to understand this prof in lecture, I could tell he was really knowledgeable and kind. I could see him getting truly frustrated when students' attentioned waned in class, but his accent is quite heavy so at some points people stopped listening.  Had super interesting guest speakers and a passion for politics!!
Also took the class ISC 2337 in English with him. Like the fact that his classes are practical. Really useful. He is really knowledgeable in his field.
This prof doesn't speak English. I really struggled to even understand a sentence.
